" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 511px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Two-dimensional transthoracic echocardiogram (2D TTE) from the subcostal view showing a normal inferior vena cava (IVD) during respiration",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 491px; height: 198px; background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    The subcostal view in a normal subject shows the inferior vena cava (IVC). Left panel: Prior to inspiration, the normal diastolic IVC diameter (arrows) is less than 20 mm. Right panel: During inspiration, the IVC collapses to less than 50 percent of its original diameter.",
"    <div class=\"footnotes\">",
"     L: liver.",
"    </div>",
"    <div class=\"reference\">",
"    </div>",
